  "texts": [
    "Hence, for supervised classification tasks, a training set with instances and their features as well as their target classes is provided, so that the model can \"learn\" the relationship between the provided features and the target class.",
    "A great variety of algorithms for such tasks exists, among them artificial neural network (ANNs).",
    "ANNs are essentially a mathematical model similar to the structure of a brain.",
    "Many small units called neurons connected to each other and structured into layers perform a series of linear and non-linear operations on the input data to derive at the desired outcome.",
    "In the case of supervised classification, the desired outcome is the target class associated with the instance."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}